The paper discusses the role of network structure in information access in online social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the study focuses on analyzing user behavior on a social news aggregator platform, which is a specific application of social networks and information retrieval, making cs.SI (social and information networks) the most likely sub-category.
